This paper focuses on developing a data-driven approach to signal detection using a distantly supervised neural network, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper utilizes recent advances in contextualized word embeddings, which suggests a possible fit with sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of neural networks also suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper's focus on identifying features that neural models may need to perform better on automatic discourse relation classification suggests a possible fit with cs.CY (Computers and Society).
